def get_secs(x):
    if x.count(':') == 2:
        h, m, s = x.split(':')
    else:
        m, s = x.split(':')
        h = 0
    secs = 3600*int(h) + 60*int(m) + int(s)
    return(secs)

df['time_seconds'] = df['time'].apply(lambda x: get_secs(x))

subset = set(df.groupby('runner_id').agg({'location':'nunique'}).sort_values('location',ascending=False).index)
#df_subset = df[df.location.isin(subset)].reset_index()
df_subset = df[df.runner_id.isin(subset)].reset_index()
df_subset['time_seconds_log_s'] = (df_subset['time_seconds_log']-df_subset['time_seconds_log'].mean())/df_subset['time_seconds_log'].std()
df_subset['runner_index'] = df_subset.runner_id.factorize()[0]
df_subset['location_index'] = df_subset.location.factorize()[0]

y = df_subset['time_seconds_log_s'].values
num_runners = df_subset.runner_id.nunique()
num_locations = df_subset.location.nunique()

location_index = tuple(df_subset['location_index'].values)

y_t = pm.Minibatch(y,10000)
runner_index_t = pm.Minibatch(runner_index,10000)
location_index_t = pm.Minibatch(location_index,10000)

with pm.Model() as simple_model:
    # Hyperpriors
#     mu_a = pm.Normal('mu_a', mu=0., sigma=1)
#     sigma_a = pm.Lognormal('sigma_a', mu=0, sigma=1)
    mu_b = pm.Normal('mu_b', mu=0., sigma=1)
    sigma_b = pm.Lognormal('sigma_b',mu=0,sigma=1)
    
    # Priors for unknown model parameters
#     a = pm.Normal('a', mu=mu_a, sigma=sigma_a, shape=num_runners)
    b = pm.Normal('b', mu=mu_b, sigma=sigma_b, shape=num_locations)
    mu = b[location_index_t]
    
    sigma = pm.Lognormal('sigma', mu=0,sigma=1)

    # Likelihood (sampling distribution) of observations
    likelihood = pm.Normal("y", mu=mu, sigma=sigma, observed=y_t)
    mean_field = pm.fit(method='advi',n=10000)

means = mean_field.bij.rmap(mean_field.mean.eval())

from scipy import stats
import seaborn as sns
varnames = set(means.keys())
#varnames.remove('a')
fig, axs = plt.subplots(nrows=len(varnames), figsize=(12, 18))
for var, ax in zip(varnames, axs):
    mu_arr = means[var]
    sigma_arr = sds[var]
    ax.set_title(var)
    for i, (mu, sigma) in enumerate(zip(mu_arr.flatten(), sigma_arr.flatten())):
        sd3 = (-4*sigma + mu, 4*sigma + mu)
        x = np.linspace(sd3[0], sd3[1], 300)
        y = stats.norm(mu, sigma).pdf(x)
        ax.plot(x, y)

with pm.Model() as simple_model:
    # Hyperpriors
    mu_a = pm.Normal('mu_a', mu=0., sigma=1)
    sigma_a = pm.Lognormal('sigma_a', mu=0, sigma=1)
    mu_b = pm.Normal('mu_b', mu=0., sigma=1)
    sigma_b = pm.Lognormal('sigma_b',mu=0,sigma=1)
    mu_c = pm.Normal('mu_c', mu=0., sigma=1)
    sigma_c = pm.Lognormal('sigma_b',mu=0,sigma=1)
    
    # Priors for unknown model parameters
    i = pm.Normal('i', mu=0, sigma=1)
    a = pm.Normal('a', mu=mu_a, sigma=sigma_a, shape=num_runners)
    b = pm.Normal('b', mu=mu_b, sigma=sigma_b, shape=num_locations)
    mu = i + a[runner_index] + b[location_index]
    
    sigma = pm.Lognormal('sigma', mu=0,sigma=1)

    # Likelihood (sampling distribution) of observations
    likelihood = pm.Normal("y", mu=mu, sigma=sigma, observed=y)
    mean_field = pm.fit(method='advi',n=10000, callbacks=[CheckParametersConvergence(diff='absolute')])
